FT  19 FEB 94 / Briefcase Q&amp;A: Supplementing a pension
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I have retired and, to supplement my pension, I propose letting two rooms in
my principal residence as bed-sits under the government scheme which allows
an annual income of Pounds 3,250 without tax liability.
1. As this is my principal residence, will letting the rooms affect the CGT
