FT  19 FEB 94 / Economic Diary: Forward events
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TODAY: Mr John Major, prime minister, meets Mr Albert Reynolds, Irish
premier, in London.
TOMORROW: Deadline for withdrawal of heavy guns around Sarajevo.
International Whaling Commission meets on Norfolk Island (until February
25). Start of two-day Financial Times conference 'Commercial aviation in the
Asia-Pacific region' in Singapore.
MONDAY: EU agriculture council meets in Brussels. Start of two-day
Japan-Russia working group on a peace treaty and the third Japan-Russia
ministerial-level consultations in Moscow. International Atomic Energy
Agency board of governors meeting in Vienna. Financial Times holds 'London
Motor Conference'. The Euro Disney banks will receive final version of an
audit of the group's finances. President's Day holiday in US.
TUESDAY: Capital expenditure and stockbuilding (fourth quarter-provisional).
UK output, income and expenditure (fourth quarter). US consumer confidence
(February); budget deficit. Walt Disney Co holds annual shareholders meeting
in Orlando. Asian Aerospace and Defence Technology Exhibition opens in
Singapore.
WEDNESDAY: European parliament in session in Brussels (until February 24).
Mr Zhu Rongji, vice-premier of China, starts visit to Japan. London Fashion
Week starts (until Saturday).
THURSDAY: Engineering sales and orders at current and constant prices
(December). Energy trends (December). New vehicle registrations (January).
US durable goods (January). EU discusses the admission of Austria, Finland,
Norway and Sweden at a special ministerial meeting in Brussels. Mr Yasuhiro
Nakasone, former Japanese prime minister, to address Chatham House in London
on the changing role of Japan. British Gas results.
FRIDAY: CBI monthly trends enquiry (February). Balance of trade with
countries outside the EU (January). Prime ministers of Finland, Sweden and
Norway meet in Helsinki. Final date for acceptance of Granada's bid for LWT.
