<HEADLINE>
FT  19 FEB 94 / Commodities and Agriculture: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
White pepper supplies in producing countries are set to remain tight at
least until August. Reports Man Producten. Meanwhile, in a week of limited
acivity becasue of the Chinese new year festivities and the Latin American
carnaval the spot price in Rotterdam was quoted at USDollars 2,825 a tonne,
nearby shipment at Dollars 2,700, cif, and new crop at Dollars 2,575. Black
pepper remained steady. Prices in India, which has hardly any carry-over
stock and is suffering from small, delayed arrivals of new crop, remained
firm. Indonesia could offer only limited quantities. Brazil's local market
remained firm in the absence of export activities. India MG-1 was quited at
Dollars 1,625 a tonne, cif, for March/April shipment; faq spot was at
Dollars 1,525, while nearby shipment was fetching Dollars 1,450, cif.
