FT  19 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Southern Radio sells 22% stake in Orchard
Media
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Southern Radio, which provides independent local radio services in
Hampshire, Sussex and Kent, has sold its 21.96 per cent stake in Orchard
Media, the commercial radio operator in Taunton and Yeovil, to Radio
Investments for Pounds 282,000.
The shares rose 9p to 111p.
Mr Rory McLeod, Southern's managing director, said the sale was part of the
group's strategy of focusing on its core business in the south-east of
England and investing in radio companies where the group could add value.
