FT  19 FEB 94 / UK Company News: HSBC selling Italian holding
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER, Banking Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
HSBC Holdings is selling its 56.6 per cent stake in Euromobiliare, the
Italian investment bank, to Credito Emiliano.
HSBC said it had agreed in principle to sell the stake, which it acquired
through the takeover of Midland Bank in 1992, for about L56bn (Pounds
22.6m). It added that negotiations were continuing, and no date for a
transfer had been set.
