said. Euromobiliare has capital markets and treasury operations, as well as
asset management, but is concentrated in domestic Italian business.
Euromobiliare shares slipped from a trading level of L2,965 after HSBC
disclosed that it had agreed with Credito Emiliano a price of L2,800 per
ordinary share, and L1,830 per non-convertible preference share.
