<TEXT>
A new row has broken out between the Irish government and the European
Commission over the allocation of IPounds 7.2bn in EU structural and
cohesion funds to Ireland for 1994-99.
A team of Commission officials, headed by Mr Eneko Landaburu, the director
general for regional policy, arrived in Dublin yesterday for what was
expected to be a stormy meeting to discuss Ireland's plans for spending the
IPounds 7.2bn under the various operational programme headings.
