<HEADLINE>
FT  18 FEB 94 / International Company News: Strong advance at Kleinwort
Benson
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER, Banking Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Kleinwort Benson yesterday confirmed high expectations for UK investment
banks by disclosing that its 1993 pre-tax profits more than doubled to
Pounds 111.7m (Dollars 168m), compared with Pounds 45.1m the previous year.
Kleinwort's 2,770 employees gained heavily from the strong trading
conditions in financial markets, and a rise in underwriting and advisory
work.
After excluding a Pounds 9.2m profit from selling Sharps Pixley, its bullion
and metals business, earnings per share rose to 56.4p, compared with 26p,
and the pre-tax return on equity rose to 26 per cent, compared with 11 per
cent.
