<TEXT>
Burns Philp, the Australian food group, has expanded in Europe with the
purchase of Karl Ostmann, the German herbs and spices producer, for DM182m
(Dollars 107m) plus a working capital adjustment expected to be about DM20m.
Mr Andrew Turnbull, Burns Philp managing director, said yesterday Ostmann
had gross annual sales of DM190m, exported to 30 countries and controlled
subsidiaries in the UK and South Africa. Latest annual net profit was
DM5.5m.
