<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Loblaw, Canada's biggest food distributor, overcame the recession and
regional price Wars in Canada to post a 17 per cent gain in profits for the
fiscal year ended January 1 1994.
Loblaw, controlled by the George Weston Group, reported net profit for the
year of CDollars 93.4m (USDollars 69.2m), or CDollars 1.07 a share, up from
