cent to CDollars 9.36bn. At the operating level, the results were strong in
both eastern and western Canada.
Fourth-quarter profit was CDollars 26.1m, or 31 cents, down from CDollars
28.8m, or 33 cents, on sales of CDollars 2.2bn, a decline of 8 per cent.
The impact of a long strike in the US supermarket unit was taken mostly in
the fourth quarter. Cineplex, a North American cinema operator and film
distributor controlled by the Montreal Bronfmans, reported its first annual
operating profit since 1987.
However, after a special charge of USDollars 7.3m, there was a final loss of
Dollars 7.4m, or 7 cents a share, against a loss of Dollars 41.3m, or 48
cents, in 1992, on sales of Dollars 546m, against Dollars 519m.
