<HEADLINE>
FT  18 FEB 94 / Observer: Taking the biscuit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An explanation arises for the number of large unwieldy sub-committees and
interminable meetings held at the Institute of Chartered Accountants in
England and Wales. A 'biscuit memo' is doing the rounds at Moorgate Place,
the institute's London bastion. It decrees no coffee for meetings that last
less than two hours, and no biscuits at all unless outside volunteers are in
attendance. Shaken rather than stirred, seems the bean-counters' response.
</TEXT>
